    <a id="wufoo-ad-graphic" class="wufoo-ad-graphic" href="http://ad.doubleclick.net/clk;270735259;98920367;x?http://www.wufoo.com/landing/1/?utm_source=csstricks&utm_medium=ppc&cmpid=brand&utm_network=d&utm_term=csstricks600x600banner">
    </a>
    <p class="note">
      As a web designer, you can build a form yourself if you want. But will it block spam? Will it look and work well on any screen size? Is it incredibly easy to make changes to? Can it accept payments? Is it multi-page with logic forks? Are you saving the data so you can build visual reports? Does that data have an API? 
      <a href="http://ad.doubleclick.net/clk;270735316;98920367;r?http://www.wufoo.com/landing/1/?utm_source=csstricks&utm_medium=ppc&cmpid=brand&utm_network=d&utm_term=csstrickstextlinkwufoo">Wufoo</a> does all that and much more. Plus it's so easy absolutely anybody can do it.

      <a href="http://ad.doubleclick.net/clk;270735352;98920367;r?http://www.wufoo.com/landing/1/?utm_source=csstricks&utm_medium=ppc&cmpid=brand&utm_network=d&utm_term=csstrickstextlinktryitfree">Try&nbsp;it&nbsp;free!</a><img src="http://ad.doubleclick.net/ad/N7439.1063086.CSS-TRICKS.COM/B7043538.2;sz=1x1;ord=2013-10-05T22:49:28+00:00?'); ?>?">
