    <div id="polls-46" class="wp-polls">
	<form id="polls_form_46" class="wp-polls-form" action="/custom-controls-in-html5-video-full-screen/?utm_content=buffer115d8&amp;utm_source=buffer&amp;utm_medium=twitter&amp;utm_campaign=Buffer" method="post">
		<p style="display: none;"><input type="hidden" id="poll_46_nonce" name="wp-polls-nonce" value="9415b958eb" /></p>
		<p style="display: none;"><input type="hidden" name="poll_id" value="46" /></p>
		<h4>Is it useful to distinguish between "web apps" and "web sites"?</h4>

<div id="polls-46-ans" class="wp-polls-ans">

<ul class="wp-polls-ul group">
		<li class="group"><input type="radio" id="poll-answer-256" name="poll_46" value="256" /> <label for="poll-answer-256">Yep. They are different things with different concerns.</label></li>
		<li class="group"><input type="radio" id="poll-answer-257" name="poll_46" value="257" /> <label for="poll-answer-257">Nope. It's all just the web.</label></li>
		</ul>

<p class="voting-buttons">

<input type="button" name="vote" value="   Vote   " class="button" onclick="poll_vote(46);" onkeypress="poll_result(46);" /> &nbsp; <a href="#ViewPollResults" class="button" onclick="poll_result(46); return false;" onkeypress="poll_result(46); return false;" title="View Results Of This Poll">View Results</a>

</p>

</div>
